---
---
<section class="problem" id="problem">
  <div class="problem-label">
    <span class="label">The Problem</span>
  </div>
  <div class="problem-body">
    <h2 class="problem-heading">
      OFF-THE-SHELF<br/>
      SOFTWARE WASN'T<br/>
      BUILT FOR<br/>
      <span class="accent">YOUR BUSINESS</span>
    </h2>
    <div class="problem-text">
      <p>
        Most enterprise software is designed for the average company. If your
        workflows, approval chains, or reporting needs don't match that average
        — and they rarely do — you spend more time working around the tool
        than with it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The result: duplicate spreadsheets, manual workarounds, fragmented
        data, and a team that's quietly given up on the system.
      </p>
      <div class="problem-stat">
        <span class="stat-number accent">73%</span>
        <span class="label">of enterprise software implementations fail to meet operational goals</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    border-bottom: var(--border);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
  }

  .problem-label {
    writing-mode: vertical-lr;
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space);
    border-right: var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .problem-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .problem-heading {
    font-size: var(--font-size-h2);
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-lg);
    border-right: var(--border);
    align-self: center;
  }

  .problem-text {
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space);
  }

  .problem-stat {
    margin-top: var(--space);
    border-top: var(--border-accent);
    padding-top: var(--space);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 4rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .problem { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .problem-label { writing-mode: horizontal-tb; transform: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: var(--border); }
    .problem-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .problem-heading { border-right: none; border-bottom: var(--border); padding: var(--space-lg); }
    .problem-text { padding: var(--space-lg); }
  }
</style>
